    "startingConditions": "Expand![Yes](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/7/77/Yes.png/24px-Yes.png) Started as a nation that can form [![Flag of Gran Colombia](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/c/c1/Gran_Colombia.png/24px-Gran_Colombia.png)](/Gran_Colombia \"Gran Colombia\") [Gran Colombia](/Gran_Colombia \"Gran Colombia\") \n\n*   Any of:\n    *    [![Flag of Colombia](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/9/98/Flag_CLM.png/24px-Flag_CLM.png)](/Colombia \"Colombia\") [Colombia](/Colombia \"Colombia\")\n    *    [![Flag of Ecuador](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/0/04/Flag_ECU.png/24px-Flag_ECU.png)](/Ecuador \"Ecuador\") [Ecuador](/Ecuador \"Ecuador\")\n    *    [![Flag of Venezuela](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/7/79/Flag_VNZ_monarchy.png/24px-Flag_VNZ_monarchy.png)](/Venezuela \"Venezuela\") [Venezuela](/Venezuela \"Venezuela\")",
    "completionRequirements": "*   ![Yes](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/7/77/Yes.png/24px-Yes.png) Playing as [![Flag of Gran Colombia](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/c/c1/Gran_Colombia.png/24px-Gran_Colombia.png)](/Gran_Colombia \"Gran Colombia\") [Gran Colombia](/Gran_Colombia \"Gran Colombia\")\n*   ![Yes](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/7/77/Yes.png/24px-Yes.png) Owns all states in the Gran Colombia, Andes, and La Plata strategic regions",
    "notes": "Forming [![Flag of Federation of the Andes](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/8/83/Flag_FND_andes_federation.png/24px-Flag_FND_andes_federation.png)](/Federation_of_the_Andes \"Federation of the Andes\") [Federation of the Andes](/Federation_of_the_Andes \"Federation of the Andes\") blocks the achievement\n\nExpand [![Flag of Colombia](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/9/98/Flag_CLM.png/24px-Flag_CLM.png)](/Colombia \"Colombia\") [New Granada](/Colombia \"Colombia\") is a good candidate to form [![Flag of Gran Colombia](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/c/c1/Gran_Colombia.png/24px-Gran_Colombia.png)](/Gran_Colombia \"Gran Colombia\") [Gran Colombia](/Gran_Colombia \"Gran Colombia\") \n\n*   They can quickly annex or subjugate their neighbors, [![Flag of Venezuela](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/7/79/Flag_VNZ_monarchy.png/24px-Flag_VNZ_monarchy.png)](/Venezuela \"Venezuela\") [Venezuela](/Venezuela \"Venezuela\") and [![Flag of Ecuador](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/0/04/Flag_ECU.png/24px-Flag_ECU.png)](/Ecuador \"Ecuador\") [Ecuador](/Ecuador \"Ecuador\"). Additionally, once [![Flag of Central America](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/2/22/Flag_UCA.png/24px-Flag_UCA.png)](/Central_America \"Central America\") [Central America](/Central_America \"Central America\") breaks up, its successors are easily annexed or subjugated. New Granada can also eventually sell the Panama Canal for £30k, giving a short-term boost to the economy.\n*    [![Flag of Mexico](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/f/f9/Flag_MEX.png/24px-Flag_MEX.png)](/Mexico \"Mexico\") [Mexico](/Mexico \"Mexico\") is an good long-term trade partner and war ally for when the player starts expanding south. Similarly, the player should befriend [![Flag of Great Britain](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/6/6e/Flag_GBR_uk.png/24px-Flag_GBR_uk.png)](/Great_Britain \"Great Britain\") [Great Britain](/Great_Britain \"Great Britain\"), [![Flag of France](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/9/92/Flag_FRA.png/24px-Flag_FRA.png)](/France \"France\") [France](/France \"France\"), and the [![Flag of America](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/7/7a/Flag_USA.png/24px-Flag_USA.png)](/America \"America\") [United States](/America \"America\") from the start, as they are otherwise likely to intervene in diplo plays during the early stages of expansion before the player has a large enough army to hold them off.\n*   When expanding southward, [![Flag of Brazil](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/0/0b/Flag_BRZ.png/24px-Flag_BRZ.png)](/Brazil \"Brazil\") [Brazil](/Brazil \"Brazil\") is a major consideration and allying them will ease the process. Conquering [![Flag of Argentina](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/3/31/Flag_ARG.png/24px-Flag_ARG.png)](/Argentina \"Argentina\") [Argentina](/Argentina \"Argentina\") and [![Flag of Chile](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/7/7d/Flag_CHL.png/24px-Flag_CHL.png)](/Chile \"Chile\") [Chile](/Chile \"Chile\") first is easier and allows for leaving the stronger [![Flag of Peru](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/5/58/Flag_PEU.png/24px-Flag_PEU.png)](/Peru \"Peru\") [Peru](/Peru \"Peru\") and [![Flag of Bolivia](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/4/4c/Flag_BOL.png/24px-Flag_BOL.png)](/Bolivia \"Bolivia\") [Bolivia](/Bolivia \"Bolivia\") who typically unite as Peru Bolivia for after.\n*   Finally, the player needs to conquer Guyana, held by three great powers. [![Flag of Great Britain](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/6/6e/Flag_GBR_uk.png/24px-Flag_GBR_uk.png)](/Great_Britain \"Great Britain\") [British](/Great_Britain \"Great Britain\") Guyana is the best to start with, as it has a land border with the state of Bolívar in Venezuela. Make sure to claim and naval invade the South Atlantic Islands (Falklands) also as those are part of the La Plata region. After that, [![Flag of Netherlands](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/6/60/Flag_NET.png/24px-Flag_NET.png)](/Netherlands \"Netherlands\") [Dutch](/Netherlands \"Netherlands\") Guyana as it neighbors British Guyana, and finally [![Flag of France](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/9/92/Flag_FRA.png/24px-Flag_FRA.png)](/France \"France\") [French](/France \"France\") Guyana. For all three Guyanas, a naval invasion is useful to bypass the enemy forces on the land border and open a second, less guarded front. With the last Guyana, it can be worth it to trade an enemy war goal, in order to get the final piece of Guyana for the achievement; however be careful not to cede any territory from the required strategic regions, even just a treaty port. Alternatively, colonize/conquer states with British/French presence (outside the required regions and held by another nation) and use \"Trade States\"."
