    "notes": "**Note:** District of Colombia and West Virginia are never counted as states for the flag, so you actually need 102 incorporated states.\n\nFighting the Civil War allows you a chance to gain Afro-American as a primary culture (requires passing [![Cultural Exclusion](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/6/65/Law_cultural_exclusion.png/24px-Law_cultural_exclusion.png)](/Power_structure_laws#Cultural_Exclusion \"Cultural Exclusion\") [Cultural Exclusion](/Power_structure_laws#Cultural_Exclusion \"Power structure laws\") or [![Multiculturalism](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/2/20/Law_multicultural.png/24px-Law_multicultural.png)](/Power_structure_laws#Multiculturalism \"Multiculturalism\") [Multiculturalism](/Power_structure_laws#Multiculturalism \"Power structure laws\") during Reconstruction), increasing the number of states which will take 10 years to incorporate (as opposed to 20). With this, all states in North America, Central America, and eastern South America can be incorporated in 10 years. Most states in western South America will take 20 years.\n\nThere are a total of 124 states between North America, Central America, the Caribbean, and South America (excluding Canada, Alaska, Hawaii, and any states owned by foreign Major/Great Powers). Mexico and Brazil are the two single countries with the most states.\n\nThis run will incur a large amount of infamy and will require proper infamy management to avoid costly wars with other Great Powers. Taking nations as Protectorate's (as opposed to direct conquering) and decreasing autonomy to Annexation will be the most infamy efficient path - especially for larger countries like Mexico and Brazil. However, managing a large number of subjects in this manner can be difficult due to Liberty Desire mechanics."
