    "completionRequirements": "![Yes](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/7/77/Yes.png/24px-Yes.png) The [![IG armed forces.png](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/b/b7/IG_armed_forces.png/24px-IG_armed_forces.png)](/Armed_forces \"Armed forces\") Armed Forces have started and completed a coup.",
    "notes": "Easiest to do as [![Flag of Ecuador](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/0/04/Flag_ECU.png/24px-Flag_ECU.png)](/Ecuador \"Ecuador\") [Ecuador](/Ecuador \"Ecuador\") as they start with Landed Voting enacted. Spam recruit and promote Armed Forces generals to make them powerful and they will start a coup to enact a more autocratic Distribution of Power law.\n\nExpandIn order for the [![IG armed forces.png](https://vic3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/b/b7/IG_armed_forces.png/24px-IG_armed_forces.png)](/Armed_forces \"Armed forces\") Armed forces (or any Interest Group) to perform a coup, they must be powerful (have more than 20% clout at any point and not drop below 18%), have less than 0 approval while also being a part of the government, and be opposed to the current Governance Principles or Distribution of Power. \n\n*   Four types of coups can occur:\n    *   Autocratic coup: Country is neither an Autocracy nor an Oligarchy and the Interest Group endorses Autocracy\n    *   Anti-Communist coup: Country is a Council Republic and the Interest Group opposes Council Republic\n    *   Anti-Republican coup: Country is either Parliamentary Republic or Presidential Republic and the Interest Group opposes Republics\n    *   Anti-Monarchist coup: Country is a Monarchy and the Interest Group opposes Monarchy\n*   The Armed Forces are usually indifferent to any of the laws described above. The only way to get them to care about the government is to wait for the leader of the armed forces to have a trait like Monarchist, Republican, Theocrat etc.\n    *   Since at game start the most countries are monarchies, the quickest way to get a coup is to restart until the leader of the armed forces has the trait Republican.\n    *   To increase the Armed Forces clout, bolster them, hire and promote their generals and admirals, expand the army, increase army funding or employ people in the military industrial complex.\n    *   To get the Armed Force's approval below 0, fire their generals or admirals, decrease their funding or pass laws that they oppose. Be careful to not push them below -10 or they might leave the government and start an insurrection. Starting in a country that already has unfavorable laws to the Armed Forces (e.g. Tripolitania) will help.\n*   The event is random and might not fire immediately even when all conditions are satisfied."
